No fewer than ten persons have reportedly been killed and others kidnapped in Bakori LGA of Katsina State by gun-wielding men who stormed the community at about 1:00 am on Tuesday. Among those abducted include the village head of the area, Mallam Umar. The hoodlums reportedly arrived at the community shooting sporadically, spreading panic among indigenes. The terrorists during the adventure raided the community, looting houses of valuables and also razing houses, cars and motorcycles, a source disclosed. The son of the village head, Umar Abdullahi was quoted to have said, â€œThey stormed our community around 1:00 am on Tuesday, throwing our community into disarray with multiple gunshots. Then went into houses and looted our belongings. They also rustled some animals and burnt down houses cars and motorcycles before taking away my father, who is our village head alongside many children and women with them. Abdullahi, however, said the hoodlums are yet to contact them or make any demand concerning those abducted. The police spokesman in the state, SP Gambo Isah confirmed the attack promising to provide more details later.